    <div class="how-it-works section" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col-lg-6  align-self-center">
            <div class="section-heading">
              <h6>How it Works</h6>
              <h2>How MoodMapper works</h2>
              <p>The program functions with the help of the <strong>Twitter API</strong> and <strong>RoBERTa.</strong> The program starts off by requiring users to register using their email, password and Twitter ID. This information is then stored in a <strong>MongoDB</strong> database and sent over to python to start pulling the tweets. The tweets are pulled using python and then analyzed using the RoBERTa model. After the tweets are analyzed, it is sent over to the database and stored. Then the data is pulled from the database and displayed to the user in the form of a website.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
